Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay near fine pink-buff. Circular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 163, 30 or 201, 3. Name Mytion. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0171.17.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0607)
